Distributed systems are becoming more and more important in current scientific and IT developments. The goal of this seminar is to get an insight into the distributed world of possibilities (such as GRID, Peer-to-Peer, parallel computing etc), solutions and open scientific problems development. Participants will have to to prepare one talk or a survey paper per semester and to take an active part in discussions.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Topics of the seminar are GRID, P2P, distributed systems and computations on these architectures. The aim is to study various distributed systems, to work with modern technical and scientific literature, to carry out tests and computer experiments, to write an overview article and to practice oral presentation skills.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students will develop the skills to carry out research in the area of distributed systems. The goal is to learn working with the most recent scientific literature in distributed systems, as well as advance the presentation and scientific writing skills.
